# =============================================================================
# LIMS APPLICATION ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# =============================================================================
# This file contains all environment variables required for the LIMS application.
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your actual values.
#
# IMPORTANT SECURITY NOTES:
# - Never commit .env.local to version control
# - The .env.local file is already in .gitignore
# - Only share credentials through secure channels
# - Rotate keys immediately if they are compromised
# =============================================================================

# =============================================================================
# SUPABASE CONFIGURATION
# =============================================================================
# Supabase is used for authentication, database, and storage.
# Get these values from: https://supabase.com/dashboard
# Navigate to: Your Project > Settings > API
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Public Supabase URL
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Location: Project Settings > API > Project URL
# Format: https://[project-ref].supabase.co
# Example: https://abcdefghijklmnop.supabase.co
#
# This URL is safe to expose in client-side code (hence the NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix).
# It's used to connect to your Supabase project from both client and server.
#
# How to find:
# 1. Go to https://supabase.com/dashboard
# 2. Select your project
# 3. Click Settings (gear icon) in the left sidebar
# 4. Click API
# 5. Copy the "Project URL" value
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Public Supabase Anonymous Key
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Location: Project Settings > API > Project API keys > anon public
# Format: Long JWT token starting with eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
# Example: eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZSIsInJlZiI6ImFiY2RlZmdoaWprbG1ub3AiLCJyb2xlIjoiYW5vbiIsImlhdCI6MTYyMzg4MzIwMCwiZXhwIjoxOTM5NDU5MjAwfQ.example_signature
#
# This key is safe to use in client-side code. It has limited permissions
# and respects Row Level Security (RLS) policies.
#
# Security features:
# - Respects RLS policies (can only access data allowed by policies)
# - Cannot bypass authentication requirements
# - Safe to expose in browser/mobile apps
# - Used for client-side Supabase operations
#
# How to find:
# 1. Go to https://supabase.com/dashboard
# 2. Select your project
# 3. Click Settings > API
# 4. Find "Project API keys" section
# 5. Copy the "anon" "public" key (click the copy icon)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Supabase Service Role Key (SENSITIVE - SERVER-SIDE ONLY)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Location: Project Settings > API > Project API keys > service_role secret
# Format: Long JWT token starting with eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
# Example: eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZSIsInJlZiI6ImFiY2RlZmdoaWprbG1ub3AiLCJyb2xlIjoic2VydmljZV9yb2xlIiwiaWF0IjoxNjIzODgzMjAwLCJleHAiOjE5Mzk0NTkyMDB9.example_signature
#
# ⚠️  CRITICAL SECURITY WARNING ⚠️
# This key has FULL ADMIN ACCESS to your database and bypasses ALL security policies!
#
# Security requirements:
# - NEVER expose this key in client-side code
# - NEVER commit this key to version control
# - NEVER share this key publicly
# - ONLY use in server-side code (API routes, server components)
# - Rotate immediately if compromised
#
# Proper usage:
# ✅ Server-side API routes (app/api/*)
# ✅ Server components (with 'use server' or in server files)
# ✅ Database migrations and admin scripts
# ❌ Client components
# ❌ Browser JavaScript
# ❌ Mobile apps
# ❌ Public repositories
#
# How to find:
# 1. Go to https://supabase.com/dashboard
# 2. Select your project
# 3. Click Settings > API
# 4. Find "Project API keys" section
# 5. Click "Reveal" next to "service_role" "secret"
# 6. Copy the revealed key (click the copy icon)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# =============================================================================
# OPTIONAL CONFIGURATION
# =============================================================================
# These variables are optional and have sensible defaults.
# Uncomment and configure if you need to customize behavior.
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Next.js Configuration
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Uncomment to customize Next.js behavior

# Node environment (development, production, test)
# NODE_ENV=development

# Port for development server (default: 3000)
# PORT=3000

# Base URL for the application (useful for absolute URLs)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Supabase Advanced Configuration
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Uncomment if you need advanced Supabase features

# Supabase Storage URL (for file uploads)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_STORAGE_URL=https://[project-ref].supabase.co/storage/v1

# Supabase Realtime URL (for real-time subscriptions)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_REALTIME_URL=wss://[project-ref].supabase.co/realtime/v1

# =============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================
# 1. Copy this file:
#    cp .env.example .env.local
#
# 2. Fill in the required values (NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL, etc.)
#    Get these from your Supabase project dashboard
#
# 3. Save the file as .env.local in the lims-app directory
#
# 4. Restart your development server if it's running:
#    Stop: Ctrl+C
#    Start: npm run dev
#
# 5. Verify the setup:
#    - Visit http://localhost:3000
#    - Try signing up or logging in
#    - Check for any connection errors
#
# For detailed setup instructions, see:
# - docs/SUPABASE_SETUP_GUIDE.md
# - README.md
# =============================================================================

# =============================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# =============================================================================
# Environment variables not loading?
# - Ensure file is named exactly .env.local (with the leading dot)
# - Ensure file is in the lims-app directory (not in a subdirectory)
# - Restart development server after making changes
# - Check for typos in variable names (they're case-sensitive)
# - Ensure no spaces around the = sign
#
# Invalid API key errors?
# - Verify you copied the complete key (they're very long, 200+ characters)
# - Ensure no extra spaces or line breaks in the key
# - Verify you're using the correct key for each variable
# - Try copying the keys again from Supabase dashboard
#
# Connection errors?
# - Verify your Supabase project is active (not paused)
# - Check that the URL includes https://
# - Ensure your internet connection is working
# - Verify the project reference in the URL is correct
#
# For more help, see:
# - docs/AUTH_TROUBLESHOOTING.md
# - docs/SUPABASE_AUTH_TROUBLESHOOTING.md
# =============================================================================
